<span id="freeTextContainer44455173770122930">This one made me really teary (a rarity for me while reading) two times during the account of what happened at Haun&apos;s Mill. It is so devastating to realize how awful things were for the early saints. Seeing the faith and goodness of the Smith family, Brigham Young, John Taylor, and so many others is just inspiring. Seeing the hated directed at the saints is just so disheartening.<br/><br/>I&apos;m really glad I&apos;m reading this series- it is really reminding me of my love for Joseph Smith. Knowing my ancestors w</span>
  <span id="freeText44455173770122930" style="display:none">This one made me really teary (a rarity for me while reading) two times during the account of what happened at Haun's Mill. It is so devastating to realize how awful things were for the early saints. Seeing the faith and goodness of the Smith family, Brigham Young, John Taylor, and so many others is just inspiring. Seeing the hated directed at the saints is just so disheartening.<br /><br />I'm really glad I'm reading this series- it is really reminding me of my love for Joseph Smith. Knowing my ancestors were in the middle of all of these stories is just unreal. </span>
